body:
This is the first commit for tSNE in dml. At the moment this is using batch gradient method which will no scale. Next step is to implement stochastic gradient method to improve performance.

Its was tested in stand alone mode. The results from the algorithm are correct. I still need to test this on distributed data. No performance stats are available at this time.

@niketanpansare @dusenberrymw @mboehm7 @nakul02

The following DML

```
print('this is a string');
print("deron's string");
print('"deron" string');
print('"deron\'s" string');
print("\"fred's\" string");
print("\"mike\'s\" string");
```

will now produce:

```
this is a string
deron's string
"deron" string
"deron's" string
"fred's" string
"mike's" string
```

Tests completed successfully [here](https://sparktc.ibmcloud.com/jenkins/job/SystemML-OnDemand/188/).

This patch addressed the issue [SYTEMML-639](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYSTEMML-639). It's small fix to recognize semicolons after user-defined function in DML. I made sure that the following example is parsed successfully.

```
x=1;print(x);
printFoo=function(int y){print(y);};z=printFoo(x);
```

Please review.

This patch adds "elif" to PyDML for addressing the [SYSTEMML-296](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYSTEMML-296). The "elif" statements are used as follows:

```
x = 6
if (x == 1):
    print('A')
elif (x == 2):
    print('B')
elif (x == 3):
    print('C')
elif (x == 4):
    print('D')
elif (x == 5):
    print('E')
else:
    print('F')
```

Please review @deroneriksson .
